===Intransitive verb===
'''expand'''
#to change from a smaller form to a larger one
#: ''Many materials expand when heated.''
#: ''This compact umbrella expands to cover a large table.''
#to increase in extent, number, volume, or scope
#to speak or write at length or in detail
#to feel generous or optimistic
#{{algebra}} to be rewriten as an equivalent sum of terms
#:''The expression <math>{(x+1)}^4</math> expands to <math>x^4 + 4x^3 + 6x^2 + 4x + 1</math>.

====Synonyms====
*(''to change from a smaller form to a larger one''): [[spread]], [[spread out]], [[unfold]]
*(''to increase the extent, number, volume, or scope of''): [[enlarge]]

====Antonyms====
*(''to change from a smaller form to a larger one''): [[contract]]
*(''to increase in extent, number, volume, or scope''): [[contract]]
*(''algebra: to rewrite as an equivalent sum of terms''): [[factor]]

